reviews.review: I liked the movie, thought they did a good job with the story telling and special affects

I liked the story as it was told, although I could give it a little more juice. The special effects were very well achieved. The movie leads you to believe that science fiction is real and that the story is in the present, very well done
Excellent movie with some great twists and plot was well played out throughout the film.

What a perfect ending to an INCREDIBLE trilogy! I LOVE this cast and I'm so sorry to hear that they've no interest in doing any more SW films due to the assinine nature of the "fanboys". It could've been about 10 minutes shorter but as a fan of the franchise from the very beginning, I couldn't have been happier.
It was a throw back to the old Star War movies. We appreciated that.

Pacing was awful from start to finish.
No conclusion to why Maz Kanata had Anakin's lightsaber.
The film ends without us knowing what Finn wanted to tell Rey.
Their "search" for the sith wayfinder was boring and lazy, they literally fall on quicksand and the map/knife happens to be there and i felt i was watching an Indiana Jones movie instead of Star Wars one.
The chosen one prophecy (one of the most important aspect of Star Wars, if not the most important) means nothing now that Palpatine was alive after Anakin/Vader's sacrifice.
I'm Rey "Skywalker" ?????????????? This is just bullshit and disrespectful.
Finally, a Star Wars film. Great ending

You can't please all of the nerds all of the time.  This film does its best to tow the line of fan service versus casual viewer.  I am in the former category (i.e. nerd), and I enjoyed this movie and thought it was a good wrap-up for the series.  Plenty of plot holes, questionable story choices, and open ends, but unless we want a 6 hour movie (or 2 parts like HP), this 2.5 hour movie does a good job of tackling that Herculean challenge. 

If you want more fan service, read the comics or the books.  Movies are for the masses and should be enjoyed as such.

But, what do I know?  I liked The Last Jedi.  :)
It was great action packed fun to go see with the family!
